"Sudoku.instructions" = "# Sudoku\n\nFill the 9×9 grid so every row, every column, and every 3×3 box contains the digits 1 through 9 exactly once.\n\n## How to play\n\n- **Tap a cell** to select it.\n- **Tap a digit** in the bottom keypad to fill the selected cell.\n- When the selected cell already contains a digit, that digit's keypad button shows a circle-slash — tap it again to clear the cell.\n- Use **notes mode** (the pencil icon) to mark candidate digits in a cell — handy for working out which numbers are still possible.\n\n## Checkpoint\n\n- Tap **Checkpoint** to start a tentative session. Every digit you place after that point is shown in a distinctive color so you can tell experiment from confirmed work.\n- The Checkpoint button then splits into **Commit** (keep the placements and clear the highlight) and **Revert** (remove every checkpoint placement and return to the state when you started the session).\n\n## Undo and Redo\n\n- Tap **Undo** to take back the most recent move. After undoing, the button splits in two so you can **Redo**.\n- Undo and redo are unlimited within the current puzzle. Making a new placement after an undo clears the redo history, and reaching the front of the timeline with Redo collapses the split button back to a single Undo.\n\n## Hints and winning\n\n- The starting clues cannot be changed.\n- The timer runs while you play. Your **best time** for each difficulty is saved.\n- Some difficulties allow **hints** — use them sparingly.\n- The puzzle is complete when every cell holds a valid digit and every row, column, and 3×3 box satisfies the no-repeat rule.";
